  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - WARRIOR</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>THE DARK ELF WARRIOR</font> - <small>Kalamandria, Bertoxxulous</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>Dont listen to all those people who say that darkelfs wouldnt make a good warrior i have manged to prove them wrong yes i know that they dont get the best strength of them all but hey at least being a darkelf 1 you look better then most barbarians and humans and 2 you have a nice good place to hunt that your not KOS too.<br>
<br>
Now i know i havent gotten too too far on the lvling scale but i have gotten to an ok point that i think i could share my opinion on warriors so that maybe ill have people who also agree with my strategy.<br>
<br>
Ok my stategy on where to fight and when and what-<br>
<br>
--lvl 1- fight in and around the first inn near the fp zone because there you have the snakes and the decaying skellys <br>
<br>
--lvl 2- stay in the EC zone and around the first inn but fight the fire bettles pawns and some of the spiderlings as you would in most places<br>
<br>
--lvl 3- at this lvl you should already be pretty good at 1h slashing and ok at kick adn dont forget to be putting the points in to the main things you will be using it will come in handy, most of the time the pawns and some decaying skelly's will drop a weapon dont be afraid to bum armor and weapons from them! and if you want to be a 2h slasher then the 1st weapon i would recommnd unless your tweaked would be the scythe, things to fight wise if you have followed this then you can take out the black bears even though most will still be yellow to you, and there is still the occasional spiderling thatll be black to you.<br>
<br>
--lvl 4- once you have lvled here then the black bears mostly should be black to you, so kill them but remember when killing the black bears that they hit fast so you need to be quick and fast to disable them before they can do too too much damage to you, so kick em right as soon as it comes back! this is the slowest lvl but at lvl 5 there is more to fight so itll go by faster.<br>
<br>
--lvl 5- at lvl 5 there are the pumas now i know what most people say is that a lvl 5 has no business being near the sand at all but go ahead try it but still you have to be quick to kick em! they hit for a bit more then the bear but they gve good exp especially if they are yellow to you which they should be, kill these until lvl 6. * a IMPORTANT reminder*  EVEN IF THE RATTLERS AND SOME ASPS ARE YELLOW TO YOU ,YOU CANNOT TAKE THEM OUT NOT UNTIL THEY ARE NEARING BLUE TO YOU THEY HIT FAST POISON AND DONT RUN UNTIL THEY ARE PRACTICALLY DEAD SO DONT TRY AT ALL!<br>
<br>
--lvl 6- at lvl 6 the pumas should be black to you but there will be the occasional black one, but get a higher lvl to take you to the skelly ruins in neriak that is the best exp you could get but make sure that the person you take can heal! then you should lvl to 7 in no time at all.<br>
<br>
--lvl 7- here you might just have to lvl by blues but i would try the skellys they should con yellow black and red try the black one and maybe a yellow if you can take it ALWAYS pull away from spawn area just incase they pop while you are fighting!<br>
<br>
--lvl 8- now here is where it gets tricky get a good weapon and you can kill lions and lionesses the best spot to hunt them would be around orc one if you are planning on being a loner only helping yourself then i wouldnt try the camp just yet that will come at later lvls. and some times if you hit fast and hard and you kic for a good ammount then you might just be able to take out a young kodiak NOT A KODIAK A
'YOUNG' KODIAK! but be careful and hope that you choose a good one because some continuously hit for 24 and it starts to take its toll after a while!<br>
<br>
--lvl 9- this is the lvl im at now but i will give that last little bit of info i have for this category kill everything blue to you especially if it says looks kinda risky but you might win! young kodiaks are good too! <br>
<br>
<br>
on the subject of worshipiing i would recommend being agnostic just because you wont be KOS everywhere that you would be if you worshiped innoruk now it isnt such a bad thing because all you have to do is say you worship innoruk that way you wont be an entire outcast or just say nothing at all about what or who you worship.<br>
<br>
<br>
-roleplaying- if you are gonna be a roleplayer then i wouldnt start shouting about your hate for all palefaces that will just make it harder for you to purchase things because to be entirely truthful most of the people who sell stuff are not DE iksar or trolls and ogres but then again if someon shouts i hate pales faces and they go n about why then you should add your see on things because there wont just be you never start the shout yourself!<br>
<br>
-grouping- warriors do well with casters and bards partly because you are expected to take ALL the hits in the grp just because you have the most HP and it is true but takeing all the hits of a good train will start to hurt which is where the casters coame in handy bards too, the bards can turn on there healing song and the casters can heal you.<br>
<br>
<br>
now this is all i ave for now but ill put more later when i have more to share now some people disagree with my way of doing things because they see it as a suicide mission of lvling and critism on everything els but ill let you decide for that
<br>
</p>

		</td></tr>
